You know. and thanks
to you and yours.

238
00:10:45.062 --> 00:10:48.565
Phil Russo and his fuckin'
gang of misfits in Jersey

239
00:10:48.732 --> 00:10:50.734
think they can go
toe-to-toe with me now.

240
00:10:51.610 --> 00:10:53.445
You know. when you do what I do.

241
00:10:53.612 --> 00:10:55.238
you're only as
strong as the asshole

242
00:10:55.405 --> 00:10:56.740
who's least scared of you.

243
00:10:56.907 --> 00:10:58.384
You know. that guy sees
a chink in the armor.

244
00:10:58.408 --> 00:11:00.786
the whole fuckin' house of
cards comes crashin' down.

245
00:11:02.120 --> 00:11:04.748
And look. t-t-tell Raq I'm done.

246
00:11:04.915 --> 00:11:06.958
No. no. no. No.
look. No more trucks.

247
00:11:07.084 --> 00:11:08.710
No more boats.
No more nothing.

248
00:11:08.877 --> 00:11:10.212
Our business is concluded.

249
00:11:10.379 --> 00:11:12.756
You're on your
own. Yo. come on.

250
00:11:12.923 --> 00:11:15.967
[scoffs] We can figure
this out. Stefano.

251
00:11:16.134 --> 00:11:18.428
[dramatic music playing]

252
00:11:18.595 --> 00:11:20.097
It don't have to be like this.

253
00:11:20.263 --> 00:11:21.473
It already is.

254
00:11:22.599 --> 00:11:24.101
[Giorgio] <i>Let's go.</i>

255
00:11:31.233 --> 00:11:33.527
I'm-I'm just telling you.
man. We can fix this.

256
00:11:46.331 --> 00:11:47.916
[music fades]

257
00:11:50.001 --> 00:11:51.503
[brakes squealing]

258
00:11:51.670 --> 00:11:53.922
[engine revving]

259
00:11:56.758 --> 00:11:57.758
[engine shuts off]

260
00:11:57.843 --> 00:12:00.303
[car door opens. closes]

261
00:12:15.902 --> 00:12:18.113
[both cars start]

262
00:12:24.661 --> 00:12:27.539
I'm sorry I ain't come around
more in the end. Grandma.

263
00:12:28.415 --> 00:12:30.041
Just didn't wanna
see you like that.

264
00:12:31.001 --> 00:12:32.836
And I ain't know
what to say. I...

265
00:12:36.715 --> 00:12:39.259
Look. I know you
said she's my moms

266
00:12:39.426 --> 00:12:40.969
and I gotta respect her...

267
00:12:42.345 --> 00:12:44.055
but too much has happened.

268
00:12:45.140 --> 00:12:47.809
I don't know exactly what
I'm gonna do. Grandma.

269
00:12:50.270 --> 00:12:52.731
I do know you gonna need
to forgive me for it.

270
00:12:52.856 --> 00:12:55.859
[somber music playing]

271
00:13:11.166 --> 00:13:13.210
[music fades]

272
00:13:23.887 --> 00:13:27.015
[ominous music playing]

273
00:13:33.730 --> 00:13:36.399
[indistinct chatter]

274
00:13:41.321 --> 00:13:42.864
I heard about Quân.

275
00:13:43.031 --> 00:13:45.492
Executed in his own casino.

276
00:13:45.659 --> 00:13:48.828
And David Kan.
Murdered in a bathroom.

277
00:13:48.995 --> 00:13:53.083
How many more people will
die because of your business?

278
00:13:53.250 --> 00:13:55.585
That gamblin' shit is way
more dirty than my work.

279
00:13:55.710 --> 00:13:57.629
And David Kan into
all sorts of bullshit.

280
00:13:58.338 --> 00:14:00.173
I don't wanna be
associated with you.

281
00:14:00.715 --> 00:14:02.509
I want you out of
my restaurants.

282
00:14:02.676 --> 00:14:04.594
And I don't care
what you do to me.

283
00:14:04.761 --> 00:14:07.347
I'm old. I want you gone.

284
00:14:07.514 --> 00:14:09.015
I told you before
that you and me.

285
00:14:09.140 --> 00:14:10.517
we in this for the long haul.

286
00:14:10.684 --> 00:14:13.270
That once you get jumped in.
you can't get jumped out.

287
00:14:13.395 --> 00:14:14.395
Look...

288
00:14:15.146 --> 00:14:16.189
I get it.

289
00:14:16.356 --> 00:14:18.358
This shit is way rockier
than we expected.

290
00:14:18.942 --> 00:14:20.735
How 'bout I give you
a couple more points.

291
00:14:20.860 --> 00:14:21.860
Double up on security.

292
00:14:21.987 --> 00:14:23.989
Turn these spots into
Fort fuckin' Knox.

293
00:14:24.155 --> 00:14:25.323
I'm done with you.

294
00:14:27.242 --> 00:14:29.119
So you sayin' you don't
care what I do to you.

295
00:14:29.286 --> 00:14:31.788
but what about the
people close to you?

296
00:14:31.955 --> 00:14:34.958
I've sent my entire
family back to China.

297
00:14:35.709 --> 00:14:37.669
I'm the only one left.

298
00:14:39.879 --> 00:14:41.673
In Chinese mythology.

299
00:14:42.424 --> 00:14:44.509
there's a monster called Hundun.

300
00:14:45.302 --> 00:14:48.138
A blind. deaf. faceless demon.

301
00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:51.725
Hundun is chaos. evil.

302
00:14:52.309 --> 00:14:55.478
corrupting and polluting
all that it touches.

303
00:14:56.229 --> 00:14:57.480
But for me...

304
00:14:58.231 --> 00:15:01.234
what's most scary about
Hundun's true evil

305
00:15:01.985 --> 00:15:03.528
isn't what it does.

306
00:15:03.987 --> 00:15:06.615
but that it can't see itself.

307
00:15:07.449 --> 00:15:10.452
It doesn't know
that it's a monster.

308
00:15:11.244 --> 00:15:13.830
Just like you.

309
00:15:15.081 --> 00:15:17.917
[tense. dramatic music playing]

310
00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:25.175
[car alarm system beeps]

311
00:15:27.135 --> 00:15:28.178
Yo.

312
00:15:29.679 --> 00:15:31.431
What the police talkin' 'bout?

313
00:15:32.182 --> 00:15:33.016
Nothing.

314
00:15:33.183 --> 00:15:35.018
What about Krystal
moms? How's she doin'?

315
00:15:37.062 --> 00:15:38.271
Hurtin'.

316
00:15:38.438 --> 00:15:39.438
Bad.

317
00:15:40.106 --> 00:15:42.817
She and Krys had they problems.
but that was still her baby.

318
00:15:42.984 --> 00:15:45.153
You was they problem. nigga.

319
00:15:48.365 --> 00:15:49.824
Maybe so.

320
00:15:53.244 --> 00:15:55.497
You gon' hit me if
you hear anything.

321
00:15:58.708 --> 00:16:00.919
[car alarm system
beeps. car door opens]

322
00:16:01.878 --> 00:16:03.505
[car engine starts]

323
00:16:04.214 --> 00:16:05.465
[siren wails in distance]

324
00:16:05.632 --> 00:16:08.093
[indistinct chatter]

325
00:16:11.680 --> 00:16:14.974
[tense music playing]

326
00:16:21.439 --> 00:16:22.607
[indistinct chatter]

327
00:16:23.191 --> 00:16:24.734
- See you later.
- Bye.

328
00:16:26.653 --> 00:16:28.071
[man 1] <i>What are we doin'?</i>

329
00:16:28.238 --> 00:16:30.091
[woman] <i>Just go around
the block. That's alright.</i>

330
00:16:30.115 --> 00:16:32.283
[man 2] <i>I don't think
they validate. hon!</i>

331
00:16:36.871 --> 00:16:38.164
[engine starts]

332
00:17:03.440 --> 00:17:04.774
[music fades]

333
00:17:04.941 --> 00:17:06.609
You really like that pizza.

334
00:17:08.987 --> 00:17:11.156
And I really don't like you.

335
00:17:11.281 --> 00:17:12.115
[chuckles]

336
00:17:12.282 --> 00:17:13.533
Give me time. I'll grow on you.

337
00:17:14.993 --> 00:17:17.036
I need to talk to
you about that girl.

338
00:17:17.829 --> 00:17:20.149
The one they found in Edgemere.
What do you know about her?

339
00:17:21.958 --> 00:17:23.334
She was just a friend.

340
00:17:23.501 --> 00:17:24.919
We were singin' together.

341
00:17:25.712 --> 00:17:27.189
The fact that you were
asking after a girl

342
00:17:27.213 --> 00:17:28.715
who just showed up dead

343
00:17:28.840 --> 00:17:31.843
makes you what we call
a person of interest.

344
00:17:31.968 --> 00:17:34.137
Get at me when you got a
fuckin' warrant. Five-O.

345
00:17:34.304 --> 00:17:35.805
Till then. fuck you.

346
00:17:38.641 --> 00:17:41.352
One of the tenants in Edgemere
said that they saw a Black woman

347
00:17:41.519 --> 00:17:44.606
leaving the apartment where we
think your friend was murdered.

348
00:17:46.941 --> 00:17:47.941
And?

349
00:17:48.985 --> 00:17:50.445
Last time I checked.

350
00:17:50.612 --> 00:17:51.988
you match that description.

351
00:17:52.155 --> 00:17:54.199
Oh shit. I do. You're right.

352
00:17:56.534 --> 00:17:58.077
Bitch-ass police.

353
00:18:08.963 --> 00:18:11.716
Your peoples keep showing
up at the morgue. Kanan.

354
00:18:11.883 --> 00:18:13.593
That doesn't bode
well for you. son.

355
00:18:14.385 --> 00:18:16.930
Keep asking these police
about all your dead friends.

356
00:18:17.096 --> 00:18:18.223
they gonna start thinking

357
00:18:18.389 --> 00:18:20.201
we might have had something
to do with that shit.

358
00:18:20.225 --> 00:18:22.578
We make a conscious effort to
stay above the proverbial fray.

359
00:18:22.602 --> 00:18:24.896
Too many questions about
unsolved murders...

360
00:18:25.647 --> 00:18:29.025
could raise a red flag
amongst our NYPD contacts.

361
00:18:30.568 --> 00:18:34.072
I'm not asking you to open
up a fuckin' task force.

362
00:18:34.656 --> 00:18:36.741
I just wanna know if these
cops are circlin' anyone.

363
00:18:36.908 --> 00:18:38.535
Hey. we'll ask around.

364
00:18:39.953 --> 00:18:41.704
So what ever happened
with what we told you

365
00:18:41.871 --> 00:18:43.790
about Raq and that
Puerto Rican kid?

366
00:18:44.374 --> 00:18:47.418
Right now. all I wanna know
is what happened to Krystal.

367
00:18:51.422 --> 00:18:54.634
[tense music playing]

368
00:19:16.573 --> 00:19:18.157
[music fades]

369
00:19:19.200 --> 00:19:21.786
Rumor has it that you paid
a visit to the tailor shop.

370
00:19:22.412 --> 00:19:25.123
'Nique said y'all talked about
the possibility of linkin' up.

371
00:19:25.290 --> 00:19:26.666
'Nique talkin'.

372
00:19:26.791 --> 00:19:27.792
I ain't say shit.

373
00:19:27.959 --> 00:19:29.210
For what it's worth.

374
00:19:29.377 --> 00:19:32.255
Pop and I think that
it's a ideal arrangement

375
00:19:32.380 --> 00:19:34.048
for all parties involved.

376
00:19:35.258 --> 00:19:36.718
Especially since we been hearin'

377
00:19:36.885 --> 00:19:39.554
Raq and these Italians
out in Queens got beef.

378
00:19:39.679 --> 00:19:41.431
Been whispers up until now.

379
00:19:41.598 --> 00:19:43.016
but shit is gettin' louder.

380
00:19:43.182 --> 00:19:46.394
Fuck does it matter to y'all
what me and 'Nique are doing?

381
00:19:46.561 --> 00:19:48.104
We want a bigger
piece of the pie

382
00:19:48.229 --> 00:19:49.230
out of Southside Jamaica.

383
00:19:49.397 --> 00:19:52.400
A portion befitting
our appetite.

384
00:19:52.525 --> 00:19:55.445
And Raq ain't cuttin'
them slices like that.

385
00:19:55.612 --> 00:19:57.447
We real hungry.

386
00:19:57.614 --> 00:20:00.033
And we got our own
supplier. Kanan.

387
00:20:00.158 --> 00:20:01.659
<i>And transportation.</i>

388
00:20:01.826 --> 00:20:03.161
Shit's turnkey.

389
00:20:03.328 --> 00:20:05.163
Just say the word. We
could be up in a day.

390
00:20:05.330 --> 00:20:07.999
[Snaps] <i>We bring together
you and Unique...</i>

391
00:20:08.833 --> 00:20:10.877
and then connect
you with our nephew.

392
00:20:11.044 --> 00:20:12.962
He just relocated
to South Jamaica

393
00:20:13.129 --> 00:20:16.299
from a very lucrative
stint in East New York.

394
00:20:16.466 --> 00:20:17.967
And we feel like...

395
00:20:20.470 --> 00:20:22.180
we could corner the market.

396
00:20:22.347 --> 00:20:24.766
What. you thinkin'
'cause I'm young

397
00:20:24.933 --> 00:20:26.809
you can control me or some shit?

398
00:20:26.976 --> 00:20:28.436
[Snaps] <i>On the contrary.</i>

399
00:20:28.603 --> 00:20:30.521
Your youth is your
greatest asset.

400
00:20:31.272 --> 00:20:34.150
You're not set in your ways.
not married to tradition

401
00:20:34.317 --> 00:20:36.277
like all of us old heads.

402
00:20:37.195 --> 00:20:39.405
You can see
opportunity we don't.

403
00:20:39.572 --> 00:20:41.532
Assuming Raq never told
you that your father

404
00:20:41.699 --> 00:20:44.369
made us a whole lot of
money back in the day.

405
00:20:44.869 --> 00:20:46.371
- [Snaps] <i>DefCon.</i>
- [Pop] <i>Hmm.</i>

406
00:20:47.205 --> 00:20:49.832
<i>He was a man of
dignity and integrity.</i>

407
00:20:49.999 --> 00:20:51.709
He was a businessman
of the highest order.

408
00:20:51.834 --> 00:20:54.504
We honor him by honoring you.

409
00:20:54.629 --> 00:20:57.548
And I'm sure you think this
is a bunch of bullshit.

410
00:20:57.674 --> 00:20:58.925
but when you get to be our age.

411
00:20:59.050 --> 00:21:01.469
<i>this is exactly the type
of shit that moves you.</i>

412
00:21:01.636 --> 00:21:04.013
It's something Raq
don't understand.

413
00:21:04.764 --> 00:21:07.642
Because when you disrespect the
niggas that come before you...

414
00:21:08.643 --> 00:21:10.436
<i>you disrespect yourself.</i>

415
00:21:11.396 --> 00:21:13.564
Legacy matters. Kanan.

416
00:21:16.609 --> 00:21:18.903
She threatened my
family. Teresa.

417
00:21:19.362 --> 00:21:20.780
My son and his mother.

418
00:21:20.905 --> 00:21:23.616
<i>And I know nobody know better
than you how that feel.</i>

419
00:21:23.783 --> 00:21:25.076
How old is Jerome?

420
00:21:25.535 --> 00:21:26.535
He's eight.

421
00:21:26.869 --> 00:21:28.538
My son just a baby still.

422
00:21:29.288 --> 00:21:32.458
There was a time when
families were off-limits.

423
00:21:33.167 --> 00:21:36.004
When wives and children
were sacrosanct.

424
00:21:36.170 --> 00:21:37.797
You know. Stefano and Raq.

425
00:21:37.964 --> 00:21:39.382
they don't care
about none of that.

426
00:21:40.133 --> 00:21:43.136
And that's why Sal and Marco
aren't wit' us anymore.

427
00:21:43.261 --> 00:21:47.974
There is not a minute.
a second that goes by

428
00:21:48.141 --> 00:21:51.561
where I don't feel my heart
broken into a million pieces.

429
00:21:53.604 --> 00:21:55.606
- I know.
- [crying]

430
00:21:55.773 --> 00:21:57.817
- I know.
- [sobbing]

431
00:21:57.984 --> 00:21:59.360
I know.

432
00:22:00.570 --> 00:22:01.571
What does Phil say?

433
00:22:01.738 --> 00:22:05.408
[tense. ominous music playing]

434
00:22:06.325 --> 00:22:08.661
He's just tellin'
me to sit tight.

435
00:22:12.790 --> 00:22:15.001
But you know I can't
do that. Teresa.

436
00:22:15.752 --> 00:22:18.087
Not when my family is in danger.

437
00:22:21.591 --> 00:22:23.426
Phil always had it in for Sally.

438
00:22:23.593 --> 00:22:25.887
Always wanted his seat. But
he was never strong enough.

439
00:22:26.054 --> 00:22:30.433
And now. he just lets
these fuckin' animals

440
00:22:30.600 --> 00:22:31.768
who killed my family

441
00:22:31.934 --> 00:22:35.313
run amok without any
repercussions at all.

442
00:22:36.689 --> 00:22:37.815
Well...

443
00:22:38.900 --> 00:22:40.943
Phil Russo is
gonna hear from me.

444
00:22:41.611 --> 00:22:44.489
Because he needs to know that
me and all of Sally's friends

445
00:22:44.655 --> 00:22:47.492
are sick of him sitting
on his fuckin' hands.

446
00:22:48.076 --> 00:22:50.119
I may not be able to
protect my family.

447
00:22:50.286 --> 00:22:52.080
but Christ as my witness.

448
00:22:52.246 --> 00:22:54.248
I am going to protect yours.

449
00:22:55.166 --> 00:22:56.584
And everyone else's.

450
00:23:02.632 --> 00:23:04.175
God bless you. baby.

451
00:23:05.426 --> 00:23:08.346
[dramatic music playing]

452
00:23:18.564 --> 00:23:20.316
[man on television]
<i>Mr. Black? Joe Louis.</i>

453
00:23:20.483 --> 00:23:21.818
[Black] <i>Well. hello.</i>

454
00:23:22.318 --> 00:23:24.195
<i>We've been expecting you.</i>

455
00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:25.613
<i>Come with me.</i>

456
00:23:28.658 --> 00:23:30.201
[knocking on door]

457
00:23:31.536 --> 00:23:33.871
<i>You been carrying that bag in
the same hand all the time?</i>

458
00:23:35.289 --> 00:23:36.582
Who there?

459
00:23:37.667 --> 00:23:40.169
[Calvin] <i>It's Calvin.
I got your food.</i>

460
00:23:41.796 --> 00:23:43.214
Fuck took you so long. man?

461
00:23:43.339 --> 00:23:45.466
[grunting]

462
00:23:46.843 --> 00:23:48.845
Shoulda dropped you
when I put down Londell.

463
00:23:49.887 --> 00:23:51.597
[rapid gunshots]

464
00:23:51.764 --> 00:23:52.932
[chatter on TV continues]

465
00:23:53.099 --> 00:23:54.899
Man. I ain't got shit
to do with none of this!

466
00:23:55.476 --> 00:23:57.019
That's what they all say. nigga.

467
00:23:57.186 --> 00:23:58.521
- [gunshots]
- [grunt]

468
00:23:58.688 --> 00:24:01.232
[chatter on TV continues]

469
00:24:03.359 --> 00:24:05.236
[Black. on TV] <i>Okay. Champ.</i>

470
00:24:05.403 --> 00:24:06.529
<i>Come on.</i>

471
00:24:07.738 --> 00:24:09.699
<i>You know you're off balance.</i>

472
00:24:12.201 --> 00:24:14.120
[door creaks. closes]

473
00:24:14.287 --> 00:24:16.664
<i>Keep that right foot
back of the left.</i>

474
00:24:30.052 --> 00:24:31.596
I know this gotta be important.

475
00:24:32.513 --> 00:24:35.683
Ain't often you reach out
sayin' we need to talk.

476
00:24:40.188 --> 00:24:41.272
It's Kanan.

477
00:24:42.023 --> 00:24:43.733
And all this shit
that's been happenin'.

478
00:24:44.734 --> 00:24:45.734
[chuckles]

479
00:24:46.277 --> 00:24:48.779
Your cousin still sayin'
that I put down Famous?

480
00:24:50.865 --> 00:24:52.825
I know you know that
I ain't do that. Juke.

481
00:24:54.577 --> 00:24:56.495
I don't know nothin'
no more. Aunt Raq.

482
00:24:57.038 --> 00:24:58.080
Are you serious?

483
00:24:59.665 --> 00:25:00.665
For real?

484
00:25:00.750 --> 00:25:02.350
You think I coulda
done that to that boy?

485
00:25:02.835 --> 00:25:04.313
That child lived with
us for almost a year

486
00:25:04.337 --> 00:25:06.631
when his mom and sister
went into that shelter.

487
00:25:07.715 --> 00:25:09.675
What you know about what
happened to Krystal?

488
00:25:12.595 --> 00:25:15.473
You know. I can almost
